  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nCut Stone\n\"Nicely squared rocks.\"\nObject Info\n10\nCrafting\n×3\nTab\nTier\nMiscellaneous\n\"cutstone\"\n“I've made them seductively smooth.”\n–Wilson\n“Perfectly squared for maximum enjoyment.”\n–Willow\n“I crush rock to make brick!”\n–Wolfgang\n“The better to mark graves with.”\n–Wendy\n“I HAVE IMPROVED THE ROCKS”\n–WX-78\n“Some smoothed rock slabs.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“Part of the Canadian shield.”\n–Woodie\n“The building blocks of civilization.”\n–Maxwell\n“Rectangular cuboid stonework with many uses.”\n–Wagstaff\n“Sölid stöne!”\n–Wigfrid\n“Squared rocks.”\n–Webber\n“I don't have to build something now, do I?”\n–Walani\n“Compressed stones, nice presentation.”\n–Warly\n“Thet be well tooled stone.”\n–Woodlegs\n“LITTLE STONES MAKETH BIGGER STONES”\n–Wilba\n“Square stones”\n–Wormwood\n“Amazing what happens when you mash a few stones together.”\n–Wheeler\n“Prepped and ready for the assembly line.”\n–Winona\n“Brick by brick, they say, they say.”\n–Wortox\n“It stone. It cut.”\n–Wurt\n“It wasn't too hard!”\n–Walter\n“Humans have been building with stone blocks for centuries.”\n–Wanda\nCut Stone is a Refined Item crafted with 3 Rocks. A Science Machine is required to unlock the recipe. Cut Stone can be used to craft various Structures. They stack up to 10, and if one makes a full stack of Cut Stone, which takes 30 Rocks to craft, it is less space-efficient than storing a full stack of 40 Rocks.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×3\n×6\n×6\n×2\n×4\n×6\n×3\n×10\n×6\nConsole versions of Don't Starve only\n×2\n×6\n×3\n×4\n×4\n×2\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×4\n×6\n×4\n×2\n×3\n×4\n×4\n×4\n×4\n×2\n×3\n×4\n×3\n×4\n×30\n×2\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nCut Stone was used to build Ice Boxes before being replaced with Gears.\nIn Reign of Giants, players use Cut Stone instead of Boards in some recipes. This is to keep some structures and items nonflammable.\nIn the old research system, the research cost of a Cut Stone was 30.\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nOriginal HD icon from Bonus Materials from CD Don't Starve.\nDSTDSRoGSWHam\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Together Craftable Items\nRegular Filters\nSurvivor Items\nWilson\nWillow\nWolfgang\nWendy\nWX-78\nWickerbottom\nWoodie\nWes\nMaxwell\nWigfrid\nWebber\nWarly\nWortox\nWormwood\nWinona\nWurt\nWalter\nWanda\nTools\nLight Sources\nPrototypers & Stations\nRefined Materials\nWeapons\nArmor\nClothing\nHealing\nMagic\nDecorations\nStructures\nStorage Solutions\nCooking\nFood & Gardening\nFishing\nSeafaring\nBeefalo Riding\nWinter Items\nSummer Items\nRain Gear\nCrafting Station Filters\nSpecial Event\nAncient Pseudoscience\nCarpentry\nCartography\nCritters\nCelestial\nBrightsmithy\nShadowcraft\nFabrication\nBottle Exchange\nCombrining Filter\nTea Brewing Filter\nSculptures\nSeasonings\nTrading\nTrading Hutch\nOfferings\nCawnival Creation\nTrinket Trove\nMad Science\nWinter's Feast Cooking\nSanctum Smithy Filter\nCustom Course Shack Filter\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Craftable Items\nTools\nLight\nSurvival\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\nAncient\nBooks\nTinkering\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve: Reign of Giants Craftable Items\nTools\nLight\nSurvival\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\nAncient\nBooks\nTinkering\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Shipwrecked and Volcano Craftable Items\nTools\nLight\nNautical\nSurvival\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\nVolcanic\nBooks\nTinkering\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Hamlet Craftable Items\nTools\nLight\nTreasure Hunting\nSurvival\nNautical\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\nGreen Thumb\nBooks\nTinkering\nCity Planning\nRenovate\nFloors\nShelves\nPlantholders\nColumns\nWall Papers\nHanging Lamps\nOrnaments\nChairs\nHome Kits\nDoors\nWindows\nRugs\nLamps\nTables",
