n|item1 = Cut Stone\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Boards\n|count2 = 1\n|result = Stone Road Turf\n|tool = Key to the City\n|dlc = Hamlet}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Cut Stone\n|count1 = 3\n|item2 = Boards\n|count2 = 4\n|item3 = Pig Skin\n|count3 = 4\n|result = Town House\n|tool = Key to the City\n|dlc = Hamlet}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Cut Stone\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Pig Skin\n|count2 = 4\n|item3 = Gold Nugget\n|count3 = 2\n|result = Swinesbury Mineral Exchange\n|tool = Key to the City\n|dlc = Hamlet}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Cut Stone\n|count1 = 3\n|item2 = Halberd\n|count2 = 1\n|item3 = Pig Skin\n|count3 = 4\n|result = Watch Tower\n|tool = Key to the City\n|dlc = Hamlet}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Cut Stone\n|count1 = 3\n|item2 = Boards\n|count2 = 4\n|item3 = Oinc\n|count3 = 30\n|result = Slanty Shanty\n|tool = Key to the City\n|dlc = Hamlet}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Cut Stone\n|tool = Pig Worker\n|result = Oinc\n|resultcount = 2\n|dlc = Hamlet}}\n\n\n== {{Pic32|Placeholder}} Trivia ==\n* Cut Stone was used to build [[Ice Box]]es before being replaced with [[Gears]].\n* In ''[[Reign of Giants]]'', players use Cut Stone instead of [[Boards]] in some recipes. This is to keep some structures and items nonflammable.\n* In the old research system, the [[Research points list|research cost]] of a Cut Stone was 30.\n== {{Pic|32|Blueprint}} Gallery ==\n<gallery>\nCD cutstone.png|Original HD icon from Bonus Materials from [[CD Don't Starve]].\n</gallery>\n{{Craftable Items}}\n[[es:Piedra cortada]]\n[[vi:Đá Mài]]\n[[Category:Refine Tab]]\n[[Category:Non-Flammable]]"
